{"id":"b1","punkte":24,"arbeitsanweisung":"Write a blog comment responding to the fictional post. Take a differentiated position, address the writer's evidence and propose a realistic school policy.","typ":"offeneSchreibaufgabe","config":{"situation":"The following blog post is fictional: ‘Our fictional study group found that students who keep their phones in another room while studying finish tasks faster. Schools should therefore ban smartphones after 6 p.m. for everyone.’ The youth platform Open Voices has invited readers to respond to this claim. Write a blog comment for its discussion page.","textsorte":"blog comment","umfangWorte":{"min":250,"max":300},"aspekte":["refer to the post’s claim and the limited evidence it presents","weigh benefits and risks of stricter phone rules","propose and justify a realistic policy for a school"]},"loesung":{"musterloesung":"The fictional post raises an important issue, but its conclusion goes too far. The study group may have observed better concentration when phones were in another room. However, this does not prove that every student needs the same rule or that schools should control students after six o’clock. The post also gives no information about the number of participants, the length of the study or the tasks they completed.

A phone-free study period can nevertheless be useful. Notifications interrupt attention, and some students find it difficult to resist checking messages. On the other hand, smartphones can support learning, for example when students use a dictionary, a calendar or an accessibility tool. A complete ban could therefore create unnecessary problems.

A more balanced policy would ask students to silence and store their phones during lessons and agreed study periods. Teachers could allow educational use when it has a clear purpose, while families would remain responsible for rules at home. This approach responds to the concentration problem without pretending that one fictional study can decide every situation.","erwartungshorizont":{"inhalt":"The comment responds directly to the fictional post, evaluates the limits of its evidence, weighs both sides and proposes a justified school policy.","struktur":"The text has a clear opening position, develops connected arguments with counter-consideration and ends with a specific, justified recommendation.","ausdruck":"The writer uses a differentiated B2 register, precise evaluative vocabulary and varied concession, contrast and cause-effect structures.","sprachrichtigkeit":"Complex sentences, verb forms, articles, spelling and punctuation are controlled well enough for a coherent B2 blog comment."}}}
